<!-- Itemo -->
<section id="itemo" class="py-16 bg-charcoal-900">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
        <div class="mb-8">
            <div class="text-accent-500 font-medium mb-2">PEER-TO-PEER MARKETPLACE</div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Itemo — Peer-to-Peer Rental Marketplace</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-charcoal-200 max-w-3xl">
                A peer-to-peer borrowing and rental platform designed to allow users to safely lend and rent everyday items. Developed from initial concept through to a fully production-ready platform, including mobile apps, payments, identity verification, and complex rental workflows.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE CHALLENGE</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">Peer-to-peer marketplaces carry inherent risk: payments between strangers, identity verification, fraud prevention, and complex lifecycle state management. Early prototypes validated the idea, but production required a complete rethink around security and reliability.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE APPROACH</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">Rebuilt with a production-first mindset. Designed auditable rental state transitions, integrated Stripe with careful webhook handling, implemented KYC checks, and built AI-powered search. Delivered a single coherent platform across web, iOS, Android, and admin tooling.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE OUTCOME</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">A fully production-ready marketplace platform with secure payment flows, identity verification, clear operational tooling via an admin dashboard, and a system designed to evolve without rewrites.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-3">KEY CAPABILITIES</div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">End-to-end product delivery</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Payments & KYC</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Trust-sensitive system design</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Complex business workflows</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Web + mobile delivery</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Wulse -->
<section id="wulse" class="py-16 bg-charcoal-800">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
        <div class="mb-8">
            <div class="text-accent-500 font-medium mb-2">ACADEMIC PLATFORM</div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Wulse — Multi-Tenant Academic Research Platform</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-charcoal-200 max-w-3xl">
                An open-source, multi-tenant academic research library designed to allow institutions to manage, distribute, and explore academic documents via a public interface. Developed from conception through to a production-ready system.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="bg-charcoal-700 border border-charcoal-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE CHALLENGE</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">Academic platforms require clear tenant separation, robust access controls, scalable document delivery, and clean public-facing UX that remains fast and discoverable. The system needed to balance institutional control with public accessibility.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-700 border border-charcoal-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE APPROACH</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">Designed a multi-tenant architecture with clear isolation boundaries. Built administrative tooling for managing institutions, documents, and metadata. Delivered a public-facing interface optimised for exploration using server-rendered architecture.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-700 border border-charcoal-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE OUTCOME</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">A flexible academic distribution platform with clear separation of concerns between tenants and users. A maintainable, extensible system suitable for open-source collaboration.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-3">KEY CAPABILITIES</div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Multi-tenant architecture</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Admin tooling</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Public UX delivery</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Server-side rendering</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Long-term maintainability</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Hydro International -->
<section id="hydro" class="py-16 bg-charcoal-900">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
        <div class="mb-8">
            <div class="text-accent-500 font-medium mb-2">LEGACY MODERNISATION</div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Hydro International — Legacy System Modernisation</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-charcoal-200 max-w-3xl">
                Hydro International relied on an internal project management and time-tracking system originally built in 2003 using a mix of C# ASP and Ruby. Brought in to modernise the system without disrupting active users or business operations.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE CHALLENGE</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">Business-critical internal tooling with an extremely old codebase. No tolerance for downtime. Existing users depended on current workflows. A full rewrite would have been risky and disruptive.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE APPROACH</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">Incremental, piecemeal migration rather than a big-bang rewrite. Rebuilt functionality gradually in modern Ruby on Rails with Hotwire. Ran old and new systems in parallel during transitions. Improved UX while preserving familiar workflows.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE OUTCOME</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100">A modern Rails 7 application running on Windows infrastructure. Zero downtime for users during migration. Improved usability and maintainability. Reduced long-term operational risk.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-3">KEY CAPABILITIES</div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Legacy modernisation</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Zero-downtime migration</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Stakeholder collaboration</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm">Progressive enhancement</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

